# Parker's Windshield Repair Website - Development Rules

## Project Overview
- Single-page website for windshield repair business
- Hosted on GitHub Pages
- Minimal, clean, professional, and modern design
- No clunky or outdated feel

## Technology Stack
- **Primary**: HTML, CSS, JavaScript (static site for GitHub Pages compatibility)


## Design Principles
- **Minimal**: Clean layouts with plenty of white space
- **Professional**: Modern typography and color schemes
- **Mobile-first**: Responsive design that works on all devices
- **Fast loading**: Optimized images and minimal dependencies
- **Accessible**: WCAG compliant for all users

## Code Standards
- Use semantic HTML5 elements
- CSS: Use modern CSS with flexbox/grid, avoid heavy frameworks
- JavaScript: Vanilla JS preferred, minimal dependencies
- Images: Optimize for web, use appropriate formats (WebP when possible)
- File naming: kebab-case for files and folders
- Comments: Clear, concise comments for complex sections

## File Structure
```
/
├── index.html
├── css/
│   └── styles.css
├── js/
│   └── main.js
├── images/
│   ├── before-after/
│   └── icons/
└── README.md
```

## Features to Implement
1. **Header**: Company name "Parker's Windshield Repair" with contact info
2. **Gallery**: Before/after image carousel with navigation arrows
3. **Reviews**: Customer testimonials section
4. **Contact**: Prominent contact information
5. **Mobile responsive**: Works perfectly on all screen sizes

## Performance Goals
- Page load time < 3 seconds
- Optimized images (max 500KB each)
- Minimal JavaScript bundle
- Fast scrolling and smooth animations

## Browser Support
- Modern browsers (Chrome, Firefox, Safari, Edge)
- Mobile browsers (iOS Safari, Chrome Mobile)
- Graceful degradation for older browsers 